name: r-mertools
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.5.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-mertools
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/merTools_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/merTools/merTools_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0044bd0968e8059434b2809de5fb5f6bd5f2cc365f8708b1c333e8e7865249cd

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-abind
    - r-arm
    - r-blme
    - r-broom
    - r-broom.mixed
    - r-dplyr
    - r-foreach
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_11
    - r-mvtnorm
    - r-shiny    
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-abind
    - r-arm
    - r-blme
    - r-broom
    - r-broom.mixed
    - r-dplyr
    - r-foreach
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_11
    - r-mvtnorm
    - r-shiny

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('merTools')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('merTools')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=merTools
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Provides methods for extracting results from mixed-effect model objects fit with the 'lme4' package. Allows construction of prediction intervals efficiently from large scale linear and generalized linear mixed-effects models.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ccwang002
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: merTools
